# Frontend SCSS Standards

## Always use design tokens

All colors, spacing, shadows, radii, fonts, and type styles **must** come from the design token files:

- `frontend/src/styles/_variables.scss` — colors, spacing, shadows, radii, layout, fonts
- `frontend/src/styles/_typography.scss` — font sizes, weights, line heights, type classes

## In SCSS files

Always `@use` the token files at the top before writing any styles:

```scss
@use '../styles/variables' as *;
@use '../styles/typography' as *;

.my-component {
  background: $color-bg;        // ✅ use token
  background: #f1f4f8;          // ❌ never hardcode
  border-radius: $radius-card;  // ✅ use token
  border-radius: 20px;          // ❌ never hardcode
  font-size: $text-base;        // ✅ use token
  font-size: 15px;              // ❌ never hardcode
}
```

## In TSX files

Use the semantic class names from `_typography.scss` directly:

```tsx
<h1>Dashboard</h1>          // ✅ h1 style auto-applied globally
<p className="body-2">...</p>   // ✅ use type class
<p className="subheading">...</p> // ✅ use type class
```

## Missing tokens

If a required style value does not exist in `_variables.scss` or `_typography.scss`:

1. **Check first** — the token may already exist under a different name
2. **If genuinely missing** — either add it to the appropriate token file, or ask the user before writing a hardcoded value
3. **Never silently hardcode** — a hardcoded value that should be a token is always wrong

## Available token files

| File | Contains |
|---|---|
| `_variables.scss` | `$color-*`, `$shadow-*`, `$radius-*`, `$spacing-*`, `$sidebar-width`, `$font-primary` |
| `_typography.scss` | `$text-*`, `$font-*`, `$leading-*`, `.h1`–`.h4`, `.body-*`, `.menu-*`, `.btn-label-*` |
